            <h2>A little bit about me...</h2>
            <p>
                Hello! My name is Sooraj Modi and I am a passionate software developer currently completing my
                Bachelor's degree in Honours Computer Science with a History minor at the University of Guelph. I love
                taking on new challenges, working on fun projects that help improve our world, and learning new things!
                My time in University, working on personal projects, and professional opportunities, have allowed me to
                grow as a person and develop essential real world skills I hope to apply towards future opportunities.
            </p>
            <p>
                A proven leader with creative problem solving skills, I strive to challenge the status quo and
                continually improve myself and the things around me. I am always looking for opportunities to improve
                and grow as a person, professional, leader, and teammate. This website showcases some of my most
                influential experiences that helped me grow into the person I am today.
            <p>
                You can find my contact information <a href="/contact">here</a>. Feel free to get in touch with me. I am
                always open to discussing new projects, creative ideas or opportunities to be a part of your vision.
            </p>
            <div class="home-sub-header">
                <h2>Some of the things I've worked on...</h2>
                <p>
                    I love programming, and over my career I have worked on numerous software projects. These projects
                    have taught so much about software development, project management, agile development, how to
                    collaborate with other developers, and creating robust, scalable, and manageable applications.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Through my professional opportunities I got to work with a numerous teams and technologies. My first
                    opportunity came with an Internet of Things (IoT) team developing a SmartCity platform. This
                    provided me invaluable experience working with Javascript, Node, Express, TDD, REST APIs, and more.
                    I was also a member of a Java development team working to improve the performance of Bell's MMS
                    service.
                </p>
                <p>
                    My personal projects have also allowed me to grow as a developer. I have used a multitude of
                    languages including Javascript, Typescript, Java, Kotlin, C, C++, Python, Elixir, Ruby, React,
                    Angular, and more. Some of the projects I am most proud of include <a
                            href="https://soorajmodi.com/blog/Botomir"
                            target="_blank">Botomir</a> a Discord Bot,
                    <a href="https://www.soorajmodi.com/blog/chicago-manual-of-style" target="_blank">Chicago Manual of
